        <h2>ABOUT TEXTREADER</h2>
    </div>
    <div>
        <h3>TEXTREADER : Convert Your text file to audio with Text-To-Speech Technology</h3>
    </div>

    <div>
        <h4>At a Glance</h4>
        <ul type="disk">
            <li>TEXTREADER technology reads aloud digital text—the words on computers, smartphones and tablets.</li>
            <li>TEXTREADER can help kids who struggle with reading.</li>
            <li>Even if you feel lazy and don't want to read,TEXTREADER will do that for you</li>
        </ul>
    </div>
    
    <div>
        <p>It a type of  assistive technology that reads digital text aloud. It’s sometimes called “read aloud” technology.

            With a click, TEXTREADER can take words on a computer or other digital device and convert them into audio. It is very helpful for kids who struggle with reading. But it can also help kids with writing and editing, and even focusing. </p>
    </div>
    <div>
        <h4>How TEXTREADER Works</h4>
        <p>TEXTREADER works with nearly every personal digital device, including computers, smartphones and tablets. All kinds of text files can be read aloud, including Word and Pages documents.</p>

        <p>  The voice in TEXTREADER is computer-generated, and reading speed can usually be sped up or slowed down. Voice quality varies, but some voices sound human.</p>
    </div>
    <div>
        <h4>How TEXTREADER Can be Helpful</h4>
        <p>Print materials in the classroom—like books and handouts—can create obstacles for kids with reading issues. That’s because   some kids struggle with  and understanding printed words on the page. Using digital text with TEXTREADER helps remove these barriers. </p>

        <p> Want to relax and enjoy you teatime while listening to you favourite genre? The no dought TEXTREDER can be your go to place. </p>

        <p> TEXTREADER lets kids both see and hear text when reading, it creates a multisensory reading experience. Researchers have found that the combination of seeing and hearing text when reading:</p>
    </div>
    <div>
        <ul type="disk">
            <li>Improves word recognition</li>
            <li>Increases the ability to pay attention and remember information while reading</li>
            <li>Allows kids to focus on comprehension instead of sounding out words</li>
            <li>Increases kids’ staying power for reading assignments</li>
            <li>Helps kids recognize and fix errors in their own writing</li>

        </ul>
    </div>
    
